{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":877,"text":"As a scientist, and also as a human being,"},{"time":4120,"text":"I've been trying to make myself"},{"time":6124,"text":"susceptible to wonder."},{"time":9499,"text":"I think Jason Webley last night called it"},{"time":12368,"text":"\"conspiring to be part of the magic.\""},{"time":16395,"text":"So it's fortunate that my career as a biologist"},{"time":19216,"text":"lets me dive deeply into the lives"},{"time":21860,"text":"of some truly wondrous creatures"},{"time":24378,"text":"that share our planet:"},{"time":26757,"text":"fireflies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28452,"text":"Now, for many of you, I know that fireflies"},{"time":30735,"text":"might conjure up some really great memories:"},{"time":33478,"text":"childhood, summertime,"},{"time":36532,"text":"even other TED Talks."},{"time":38302,"text":"Maybe something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45360,"text":"My seduction into the world of fireflies"},{"time":47815,"text":"began when I was back in graduate school."},{"time":51664,"text":"One evening, I was sitting out in my backyard"},{"time":54488,"text":"in North Carolina,"},{"time":56426,"text":"and suddenly, these silent sparks"},{"time":61725,"text":"rose up all around me,"},{"time":63579,"text":"and I began to wonder:"},{"time":64961,"text":"How do these creatures make light,"},{"time":67651,"text":"and what's with all this flashing?"},{"time":69341,"text":"Are they talking to one another?"},{"time":71180,"text":"And what happens after the lights go out?"},{"time":74371,"text":"I've been lucky enough to answer"},{"time":75662,"text":"some of these questions"},{"time":77030,"text":"as I've explored this nocturnal world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81121,"text":"Now if you've ever seen"},{"time":83460,"text":"or even heard about fireflies,"},{"time":85561,"text":"then you'll know how magically they can transform"},{"time":88207,"text":"our everyday landscape into something"},{"time":90598,"text":"ethereal and otherworldly,"},{"time":92501,"text":"and this happens around the globe,"},{"time":94442,"text":"like this hillside in the Smoky Mountains"},{"time":96532,"text":"that I saw transformed into a living cascade of light"},{"time":100618,"text":"by the eerie glows of these blue ghost fireflies,"},{"time":104978,"text":"or a roadside river that I visited in Japan"},{"time":107998,"text":"as it was giving birth to the slow, floating flashes"},{"time":112104,"text":"of these Genji fireflies,"},{"time":114735,"text":"or in Malaysia, the mangrove trees"},{"time":117297,"text":"that I watched blossom nightly"},{"time":119625,"text":"not with flowers"},{"time":121055,"text":"but with the lights of a thousand — \n(Bleep! Bleep!) — fireflies,"},{"time":123923,"text":"all blinking together"},{"time":125253,"text":"in stunning synchrony."},{"time":128411,"text":"These luminous landscapes"},{"time":130507,"text":"still fill me with wonder,"},{"time":132899,"text":"and they keep me connected to the magic"},{"time":135419,"text":"of the natural world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137827,"text":"And I find it amazing that they're created"},{"time":139443,"text":"by these tiny insects."},{"time":142731,"text":"In person, fireflies are charming."},{"time":145622,"text":"They're charismatic."},{"time":147435,"text":"They've been celebrated in art"},{"time":149119,"text":"and in poetry for centuries."},{"time":151594,"text":"As I've traveled around the world,"},{"time":152992,"text":"I've met many thoughtful people"},{"time":155010,"text":"who have told me that God put fireflies on Earth"},{"time":157839,"text":"for humans to enjoy."},{"time":159990,"text":"Other creatures can enjoy them too."},{"time":162386,"text":"I think these graceful insects are truly miraculous"},{"time":166715,"text":"because they so beautifully illuminate"},{"time":170720,"text":"the creative improvisation of evolution."},{"time":174951,"text":"They've been shaped by two powerful"},{"time":176761,"text":"evolutionary forces:"},{"time":178292,"text":"natural selection, the struggle for survival,"},{"time":181952,"text":"and sexual selection,"},{"time":184101,"text":"the struggle for reproductive opportunity."},{"time":188162,"text":"As a firefly junkie, the past 20 years"},{"time":190513,"text":"have been quite an exciting ride."},{"time":192999,"text":"Together with my students at Tufts University"},{"time":195496,"text":"and other colleagues,"},{"time":196512,"text":"we've made lots of new discoveries about fireflies:"},{"time":200119,"text":"their courtship and sex lives,"},{"time":202128,"text":"their treachery and murder."},{"time":205022,"text":"So today I'd like to share with you"},{"time":206839,"text":"just a couple of tales that we've brought back"},{"time":209310,"text":"from our collective adventures"},{"time":211788,"text":"into this hidden world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215498,"text":"Fireflies belong to a very beautiful"},{"time":218660,"text":"and diverse group of insects, the beetles."},{"time":222898,"text":"Worldwide, there are more than 2,000 firefly species,"},{"time":227511,"text":"and these have evolved remarkably diverse"},{"time":229671,"text":"courtship signals,"},{"time":231026,"text":"that is, different ways to find and attract mates."},{"time":234660,"text":"Around 150 million years ago,"},{"time":236916,"text":"the very first fireflies probably looked like this."},{"time":240045,"text":"They flew during the daytime"},{"time":241402,"text":"and they didn't light up."},{"time":243665,"text":"Instead, males used their fantastic antennae"},{"time":246838,"text":"to sniff out perfumes given off by their females."},{"time":250949,"text":"In other fireflies, it's only the females who light up."},{"time":254555,"text":"They are attractively plump and wingless,"},{"time":258897,"text":"so every night, they climb up onto perches"},{"time":260821,"text":"and they glow brightly for hours"},{"time":262789,"text":"to attract their flying but unlit males."},{"time":267980,"text":"In still other fireflies, both sexes"},{"time":269830,"text":"use quick, bright flashes to find their mates."},{"time":273217,"text":"Here in North America,"},{"time":274688,"text":"we have more than 100 different kinds of firefly"},{"time":277829,"text":"that have the remarkable ability to shine energy"},{"time":281406,"text":"out from their bodies"},{"time":283644,"text":"in the form of light."},{"time":285970,"text":"How do they do that?"},{"time":288420,"text":"It seems totally magical,"},{"time":290453,"text":"but these bioluminescent signals"},{"time":291736,"text":"arise from carefully orchestrated chemical reactions"},{"time":295040,"text":"that happen inside the firefly lantern."},{"time":297934,"text":"The main star is an enzyme called luciferase,"},{"time":301241,"text":"which in the course of evolution"},{"time":302996,"text":"has figured out a way to wrap its tiny arms"},{"time":306190,"text":"around an even smaller molecule called luciferin,"},{"time":309780,"text":"in the process getting it so excited"},{"time":312457,"text":"that it actually gives off light."},{"time":315831,"text":"Incredible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317506,"text":"But how could these bright lights"},{"time":319334,"text":"have benefited some proto-firefly?"},{"time":323479,"text":"To answer this question, we need to flip back"},{"time":325589,"text":"in the family album to some baby pictures."},{"time":329953,"text":"Fireflies completely reinvent\ntheir bodies as they grow."},{"time":333665,"text":"They spend the vast majority of their lifetime,"},{"time":335966,"text":"up to two years,"},{"time":337709,"text":"in this larval form."},{"time":340570,"text":"Their main goal here, like my teenagers,"},{"time":342823,"text":"is to eat and grow."},{"time":345978,"text":"And firefly light first originated"},{"time":348430,"text":"in these juveniles."},{"time":350477,"text":"Every single firefly larva can light up,"},{"time":352907,"text":"even when their adults can't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355786,"text":"But what's the point"},{"time":356878,"text":"to being so conspicuous?"},{"time":360515,"text":"Well, we know that these juveniles"},{"time":362133,"text":"make nasty-tasting chemicals"},{"time":364113,"text":"that help them survive their extended childhood,"},{"time":367731,"text":"so we think these lights first evolved as a warning,"},{"time":371561,"text":"a neon sign that says, \"Toxic! Stay away!\""},{"time":376120,"text":"to any would-be predators."},{"time":379014,"text":"It took many millions of years"},{"time":381964,"text":"before these bright lights"},{"time":383363,"text":"evolved into a smart communication tool"},{"time":385901,"text":"that could be used not just to\nward off potential predators"},{"time":388916,"text":"but to bring in potential mates."},{"time":391886,"text":"Driven now by sexual selection,"},{"time":394687,"text":"some adult fireflies"},{"time":396577,"text":"like this proud male"},{"time":398973,"text":"evolved a shiny new glow-in-the-dark lantern"},{"time":402765,"text":"that would let them take courtship"},{"time":404609,"text":"to a whole new level."},{"time":408389,"text":"These adults only live a few weeks,"},{"time":410841,"text":"and now they're single-mindedly focused on sex,"},{"time":415757,"text":"that is, on propelling their genes"},{"time":417727,"text":"into the next firefly generation."},{"time":420503,"text":"So we can follow this male out into the field"},{"time":423767,"text":"as he joins hundreds of other males"},{"time":426791,"text":"who are all showing off their new courtship signals."},{"time":431169,"text":"It's amazing to think that the luminous displays"},{"time":434161,"text":"we admire"},{"time":435845,"text":"here and in fact everywhere around the world"},{"time":438280,"text":"are actually the silent love songs"},{"time":442476,"text":"of male fireflies."},{"time":445453,"text":"They're flying and flashing their hearts out."},{"time":449540,"text":"I still find it very romantic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453080,"text":"But meanwhile, where are all the females?"},{"time":456497,"text":"Well, they're lounging down below"},{"time":458092,"text":"surveying their options."},{"time":459830,"text":"They have plenty of males to choose from,"},{"time":461758,"text":"and these females turn out to be very picky."},{"time":465850,"text":"When a female sees a flash"},{"time":468215,"text":"from an especially attractive male,"},{"time":470862,"text":"she'll aim her lantern in his direction,"},{"time":473843,"text":"and give him a flash back."},{"time":476370,"text":"It's her \"come hither\" sign."},{"time":479771,"text":"So he flies closer and he flashes again."},{"time":483366,"text":"If she still likes him,"},{"time":484492,"text":"they'll strike up a conversation."},{"time":487703,"text":"These creatures speak their love"},{"time":490395,"text":"in the language of light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493298,"text":"So what exactly do these females consider sexy?"},{"time":498195,"text":"We decided to conduct some firefly opinion polls"},{"time":500940,"text":"to find out."},{"time":502702,"text":"When we tested females using blinking LED lights,"},{"time":505910,"text":"we discovered they prefer males"},{"time":508225,"text":"who give longer-lasting flashes."},{"time":512280,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":515891,"text":"I know you're wondering,"},{"time":517070,"text":"what gives these males their sex appeal?"},{"time":520273,"text":"Now we get to see what happens"},{"time":521648,"text":"when the lights go out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524209,"text":"The first thing we discovered"},{"time":525678,"text":"is that once a male and female hook up like this,"},{"time":528447,"text":"they stay together all night long,"},{"time":531192,"text":"and when we looked inside"},{"time":532419,"text":"to see what might be happening,"},{"time":533853,"text":"we discovered a surprising new twist"},{"time":536141,"text":"to firefly sex."},{"time":538105,"text":"While they're mating,"},{"time":539275,"text":"the male is busy giving the female"},{"time":541079,"text":"not just his sperm"},{"time":543050,"text":"but also a nutrient-filled package"},{"time":547156,"text":"called a nuptial gift."},{"time":551777,"text":"We can zoom in to look more closely"},{"time":553711,"text":"inside this mating pair."},{"time":555274,"text":"We can actually see the gift —"},{"time":556967,"text":"it's shown here in red —"},{"time":558379,"text":"as it's being passed from the male to the female."},{"time":562329,"text":"What makes this gift so valuable"},{"time":565464,"text":"is that it's packed with protein"},{"time":567320,"text":"that the female will use to provision her eggs."},{"time":571781,"text":"So females are keeping their eyes on this prize"},{"time":575651,"text":"as they size up potential mates."},{"time":577923,"text":"We discovered that females use male flash signals"},{"time":580792,"text":"to try to predict which males"},{"time":582839,"text":"have the biggest gifts to offer,"},{"time":584909,"text":"because this bling helps the female lay more eggs"},{"time":589746,"text":"and ultimately launch more of her own offspring"},{"time":592997,"text":"into the next generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597687,"text":"So it's not all sweetness and light."},{"time":599695,"text":"Firefly romance is risky."},{"time":602466,"text":"For the most part, these adult fireflies"},{"time":604943,"text":"don't get eaten because like their juveniles"},{"time":607627,"text":"they can manufacture toxins that are repellent"},{"time":610563,"text":"to birds and other insectivores,"},{"time":613620,"text":"but somewhere along the line,"},{"time":616120,"text":"one particular group of fireflies"},{"time":618440,"text":"somehow lost the metabolic machinery"},{"time":621567,"text":"needed to make their own protective toxins."},{"time":625370,"text":"This evolutionary flaw,"},{"time":627650,"text":"which was discovered by my colleague Tom Eisner,"},{"time":630356,"text":"has driven these fireflies"},{"time":632299,"text":"to take their bright lights out into the night"},{"time":635697,"text":"with treacherous intent."},{"time":639380,"text":"Dubbed \"femme fatales\""},{"time":641010,"text":"by Jim Lloyd, another colleague,"},{"time":643495,"text":"these females have figured out how to target"},{"time":646413,"text":"the males of other firefly species."},{"time":650224,"text":"So the hunt begins with the predator —"},{"time":652124,"text":"she's shown here in the lower left —"},{"time":654171,"text":"where she's sitting quietly"},{"time":656218,"text":"and eavesdropping on the courtship conversation"},{"time":659350,"text":"of her intended prey,"},{"time":660790,"text":"and here's how it might go."},{"time":662803,"text":"First the prey male flashes, \"Do you love me?\""},{"time":666673,"text":"His own female responds, \"Maybe.\""},{"time":670779,"text":"So then he flashes again."},{"time":673605,"text":"But this time, the predator sneaks in a reply"},{"time":677158,"text":"that cleverly mimics exactly\nwhat the other female just said."},{"time":682834,"text":"She's not looking for love: she's looking for toxins."},{"time":687300,"text":"If she's good, she can lure this male close enough"},{"time":691181,"text":"to reach out and grab him,"},{"time":694172,"text":"and he's not just a light snack."},{"time":696613,"text":"Over the next hour, she slowly"},{"time":699448,"text":"exsanguinates this male"},{"time":702307,"text":"leaving behind just some gory remains."},{"time":706000,"text":"Unable to make their own toxins,"},{"time":708751,"text":"these females resort to drinking the blood"},{"time":711088,"text":"of other fireflies to get these protective chemicals."},{"time":715783,"text":"So a firefly vampire,"},{"time":721628,"text":"brought to you by natural selection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725980,"text":"We still have a lot to learn about fireflies,"},{"time":729161,"text":"but it looks like many stories will remain untold,"},{"time":732544,"text":"because around the world, firefly populations"},{"time":734973,"text":"are blinking out."},{"time":737628,"text":"The main culprit: habitat loss."},{"time":740216,"text":"Pretty much everywhere, the fields and forests,"},{"time":742702,"text":"the mangroves and meadows\nthat fireflies need to survive,"},{"time":745649,"text":"are giving way to development and to sprawl."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749281,"text":"Here's another problem: we've conquered darkness,"},{"time":753470,"text":"but in the process, we spill so\nmuch extra light out into the night"},{"time":756964,"text":"that it disrupts the lives of other creatures,"},{"time":760090,"text":"and fireflies are especially sensitive to light pollution"},{"time":763534,"text":"because it obscures the signals"},{"time":766155,"text":"that they use to find their mates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770614,"text":"Do we really need fireflies?"},{"time":772592,"text":"After all, they're just one tiny bit"},{"time":774631,"text":"of Earth's biodiversity."},{"time":776900,"text":"Yet every time a species is lost,"},{"time":780208,"text":"it's like extinguishing a room full of candles"},{"time":782897,"text":"one by one."},{"time":785825,"text":"You might not notice"},{"time":786771,"text":"when the first few flames flicker out,"},{"time":790061,"text":"but in the end, you're left sitting in darkness."},{"time":799591,"text":"As we work together to craft a planetary future,"},{"time":804411,"text":"I hope we can find a way"},{"time":806875,"text":"to keep these bright lights shining."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810328,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812364,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}